(20034, 31, 'fill_blank', NULL, NULL, 'adaptation', NULL, '[note]\n# Inclusive design\n## Definition\n● Designing products that can be accessed by a diverse range of people without the need for any {Q31}\n● Not the same as universal design: that is design for everyone, including catering for people with {Q32} problems.\n## Examples of inclusive design\n● {Q33} which are adjustable, avoiding back or neck problems\n● {Q34} in public toilets which are easier to use\n● To assist the elderly:\n○ designers avoid using {Q35} in interfaces\n○ people can make commands using a mouse, keyboard or their {Q36}\n## Impact of non-inclusive designs\n● Access\n○ Loss of independence for disabled people.\n● Safety\n○ Seatbelts are especially problematic for {Q37} women.\n○ PPE jackets are often unsuitable because of the size of women\'s {Q38}\n○ PPE for female {Q39} officers dealing with emergencies is the worst.\n● Comfort in the workplace\n○ The {Q40} in offices is often too low for women.', 1, NULL, NOW());
